post_Description:
scaled and icy was created and born in a time of uncertainty.
live shows were always an important part of our dna as a band. we probably wouldn’t even exist with out them. we always wrote songs for the show, never the other way around. but i always wondered what it would be like to write a record that never existed in a concert setting.
then we had no choice but to write that kind of record. so that’s what we tried.
as the songs took shape, and we released them, and sat at home, we felt proud. proud of our fans, mostly. it felt good to release music. but something was off. i wondered, what would happen to these songs if we let them echo through a venue?
and then, slowly, live music began to dust itself off.

71 shows and 14 countries later, scaled and icy became something different. the lyrics meant something different, something more, the colors found their purpose, the chords rubbed together differently. the record came to life.
it was confirmed: this band and these specific songs needed live music.

i want to thank our crew, who took us around the world during one of the toughest eras of touring ever.
this past album cycle has meant so much to me.
and you, you resilient bunch of my favorite people, you brought this to life and continue to support it. you have given me purpose, humility, and pride. you guys have given me so much. thank you.

and that concludes ψ

post_Description:
Дякую вам за фідбек на мою нову пісню «Душа».

Хочу розповісти трохи більше про центрального персонажа кліпу - прообраз жінки-берегині, давній український оберіг - вузликову ляльку-мотанку.

З давніх-давен мотанка була сильним захистом душ від усіх бід. Завжди приносила в дім мир та надію на світле майбутнє. І для мене було важливо принести цю енергію в серця слухачів.Тому у нашу мотанку, яку дбайливо створила власноруч @yana.dereza, вкладено багато сенсів.

Поступово буду знайомити вас з усім символізмом, вкладеним в цю надзвичайну роботу 🙏🏼

Тому залишайтеся на зв‘язку, дивіться відео та слухайте пісню «Душа» на всіх цифрових майданчиках ❣️

user_Description:
NK | Nastia Kamenskykh

Тур українськими містами «Я-Україна» 🇺🇦👇🏼
karabas.com/ua/tours/nk-tour
post_Description:
Здавна наші пращури вважали, що душа - дзеркало внутрішнього світу людини, в якому захований цілий Всесвіт. Зв’язок із нашим минулим та сучасним, який таїться в ДНК нашого народу. Це наймогутніші сили природи, що збиралися воєдино, аби зміцнити наші віру та любов.

Сьогодні я презентую пісню «Душа», в якій оспівую сильну та вольовиту душу українського народу. Я знаю, що сьогодні більшість українців відчули особливий потяг до вивчення свого коріння, бажання пізнати українську культуру глибше та дослідити насліддя попередніх поколінь. Тому у відео нам хотілося підкреслити фольклорні мотиви пісні та переплести важливі елементи української культури. Кожна деталь занурює в глибини нашого етносу.
Просто відчуйте.

Була дуже рада зробити сюрприз та разом чудово провести час з вихованцями проєкту для маленьких українців, які мають особливі потреби «Особливі Українці. Діти» 💙

На майстер-класі, організованому @gosensorica в українському культурному центрі «Джерело» з такою патріотичною назвою «Я люблю Україну», ми зробили долоньки, на яких написали наші найзаповітніші мрії, створили велике синьо-жовте серце, намалювали малюнки, а неймовірний «потяг незламності», який зробив Артем з Харкова @gosensorica передали до міжнародної спілки студентів ESADE, які погодилися підтримати проєкт своїми донатами.

Щоразу, долучаючись до таких подій, не можу не висловлювати захоплення силою та стійкістю батьків, а також їх неймовірно талановитими, щирими та відкритими дітками 💛

Дуже дякую за запрошення та залишаю в сторіс посилання, якщо у вас також є бажання підтримати проєкт 🙌🏼

Nos emociona mucho contarles sobre este proyecto en el que creemos y en el que hemos estado trabajando con el corazón. Bilateral fue muy especial para uds y para nosotras, y ahora queremos darles algo diferente, más cercano a nuestro alma, mucho más profundo y humano. Human Of Interest es eso. 📁🔍📇🎙️🖤 Lo podrán escuchar en todas las plataformas, y además, video exclusivo de cada capítulo en nuestro canal de Youtube. Con 2 episodios mensuales, y con invitados espectaculares. ✨

Próximo lunes 13: estreno.

Todos somos un caso sin resolver, y en Human Of Interest, buscamos investigarnos. Todos hemos sido testigos de los triunfos y del caso de éxito de cada uno de nuestros invitados, ha sido evidente, pero queremos indagar más en su trasfondo humano.
Hablaremos de esas cosas que no se suelen tocar en público, de las que no se suele preguntar, ni mencionar. Buscando profundidad, viendo, por primera vez, lo que está en la sombra, en la evidencia que, intencionalmente o subconscientemente, evadimos. Será una interrogación cálida y divertida, en donde nos mostrarán su evidencia más cercana al corazón, con ayuda de testigos que los aman, y escucharemos sus propios testimonios sobre quiénes son.

Filmmaker: @andrescifuentesmartinez

Je suis très heureux de rejoindre le projet du Comptoir Immobilier Sport Business ! 😊

Après avoir refermé la page du terrain, je suis très attaché aux sujets qui concernent la transmission pour accompagner les plus jeunes. La préparation de l’après-carrière est un enjeu fondamental pour les athlètes lorsqu’ils sont en activité. Faire les bons choix sur ces sujets peut changer positivement leurs vies et celles de leurs familles

👉 C’est pourquoi je m’associe au Comptoir Immobilier qui accompagne les investisseurs dans l’immobilier depuis 27 ans au travers de partenariats bancaires. Ils ont déjà conseillé + de 200 sportifs tant sur le plan de leur reconversion que sur la gestion de patrimoine. 92% des clients sont satisfaits de leurs investissements!

👉 Les carrières et les questions étant différentes d’un athlète à l’autre,
Le Comptoir Immobilier Sport Business fait le choix de proposer des solutions immobilières sur-mesure et des investissements en Private Equity Immobilier.

Je remercie Roland Mifort, directeur du Comptoir Immobilier, pour sa confiance, et j’ai hâte de collaborer avec les équipes, leurs partenaires bancaires et leurs clients.

post_Description:
meu amor, vc trintou!
e quanta história carrega dentro de si, né?

a gente se conheceu em um momento muito conturbado da minha vida. a verdade, é que eu já tinha me conformado que a paz não tinha sido reservada pra mim.

vivia na confusão, na correria, na ansiedade. acostumada com o caos. normalizando o desconforto e a angústia.

foi aí que a sorte (chame isso do que quiser) brilhou. sorte de ter te encontrado tão cedo na vida.

vc apareceu no meu momento mais difícil, apareceu exatamente no momento que eu mais precisava.

sempre fui muito sozinha. desde cedo entendi que enfrentaria minhas batalhas sem poder me apoiar muito em alguém. e ter sido supreendida com um parceiro que eu posso contar pra tudo foi uma novidade.

alguém que eu pudesse confiar meus segredos mais íntimos, alguém que eu pudesse pedir ajuda em situações que pareciam impossíveis de resolver, alguém que me abraçasse quando o desespero não cabia mais no meu peito.

e quantas vezes a gente já se apoiou, né?
as pessoas costumam ver nossos ápices, nossas risadas, nossa alegria..
mas e quando a única coisa que existe é a dor? e quando a única coisa que temos para compartilhar é o choro?

vc me transformou, sou uma pessoa antes e depois de você.
independente do que o futuro nos reserva, lembre-se sempre disso.
vc me ajudou a descobrir uma versão de mim que eu jamais imaginaria conhecer.
e que felicidade poder comemorar mais um ano ao seu lado.

feliz seu dia!
te amo muito ❤️

post_Description:
El invierno ha terminando y las vacaciones de Semana Santa están a la vuelta de la esquina, una combinación perfecta para organizar una escapada y hacer un paréntesis de la rutina. Estas son algunas de las mejores regiones españolas para visitar esta primavera, según un ranking de los mejores destinos de Europa que valora las horas de sol y la idoneidad para ir de vacaciones en Semana Santa:

🧳 Alicante tiene el mayor número de horas de sol de Europa: una media de 349 al mes. Es el lugar perfecto para vivir un verano express en pleno abril

🧳 Murcia tiene un atractivo arquitectónico impactante, como la catedral de la Plaza del Cardenal Belluga o el Palacio Episcopal, además de sus playas, más tranquilas en esta época

🧳 Málaga ofrece una gran variedad de hoteles, complejos turísticos y playas de arena. Además, sus procesiones tradicionales de Semana Santa son muy reconocidas y emocionantes, especialmente la Procesión del Cristo de Mena, la más famosa

🧳 Las Islas Canarias, destacando Lanzarote, Gran Canaria y Tenerife, tienen temperaturas de entre 20 y 25˚ grados entre marzo y mayo. Es el momento para visitar su naturaleza y playas sin tantos turistas

🧳 Granada es un destino perfecto para la primavera: puedes visitar su famosa arquitectura medieval (con especial mención a la Alhambra), los palacios reales, con sus patios y fuentes, y los huertos en los jardines del Generalife, que en esta época están rodeados de flores y vegetación, todo con una temperatura agradable

🧳 Las Islas Baleares, en concreto Ibiza, pues en primavera su campiña está florecida y se puede pasear tranquilamente por las calas escondidas y sus pueblos, sin el ajetreo del verano. Mallorca, por su parte, goza de temperaturas que oscilan entre los 20 y los 25˚ en el sur, y el mar está en su color aguamarina más puro

🧳 Sevilla es un destino idóneo para visitar en primavera: es cuando los parques y los naranjos que adornan el casco antiguo florecen, las temperaturas aún no son extremas y se celebra la Feria de Abril

¿Qué otro destino nacional incluirías? Todos los lugares, de España y fuera, que aparecen en el ranking, en el link de la bio.

#viajar #semanasanta #travelspain

we want to clothe you in that goodness this Valentine’s Day! Check out our new pajamas from @words_bysadierob - your Galentines day party isn’t ready for the cuteness 💗💗💗

post_Description: #tbt My love of hair has been my north star my whole life. In addition of figure skaters, iconic hair dressers were people I grew up idolizing. Sasson , Rechelbacher, Fekei, Hershberger, Eber. Never in 1 million years when I was in beauty school 17 years ago did I think I would ever found a haircare brand of my own. Beyond my wildest dreams. When I think about everything I have gone through and everything I had to do to get to this point @jvnhair is one of my proudest accomplishments. From formulas, performance, marketing, social media, packaging, copy, ingredients I have infused a lifetime of passion and curiosity amidst one of the most challenging environments possible, a global pandemic & we wound up in @sephora 🥹 a place that has been my playground for decades. I have been working on JVN Hair for almost 4 years and I am just so proud of our team, myself, our scientists, every person who has helped us in anyway. To other queer people out there keep going. Keep creating. Keep dreaming big. I have always tried to channel my energy towards things I am passionate about; things I have always loved is the individuality, expression, and art that is our hair. Love y’all so big ❤️ #jvnhair #entrepeneur #business #haircare #beauty

Bad Blood

📽 by @wildlife_abbie

In this one of a kind video, captured during a safari in South Africa's greater Kruger area in February 2023, a group of tourists found themselves unexpectedly caught up in a dramatic scene involving a herd of elephants. Initially, the atmosphere was calm as the visitors enjoyed observing the relaxed elephants. However, the tranquility was shattered when a young female elephant suddenly t-boned her brother, causing him to fall onto his back and cry out for assistance.

In response, the mother elephants rushed to the young one's aid, but in the chaos, they mistakenly perceived the tourists and their vehicle as the source of the disturbance. This misunderstanding led to a tense standoff between the protective elephants and the safari guide. Fortunately, the experienced guide managed to diffuse the situation and reassure the agitated herd, averting any potential danger.

Ultimately, everyone emerged from the encounter unscathed, although the young elephant that was knocked over likely suffered some bruises from the unexpected tumble.

post_Description:
Patterning

📽 by @Paulyk5

Demonstrating a keen awareness of its prey's behavior, the coyote seizes every opportunity to stealthily close the distance between itself and the target.

Patterning refers to the process by which a predator observes and analyzes the behavior, movements, and habits of its prey to determine the most opportune moment to strike. By studying the target's patterns, predators can anticipate their movements, minimize the risk of detection, and increase their chances of a successful hunt.

Humans use pattern recognition as well. As an essential aspect of their training, boxers examine their opponent’s previous fights to observe their fighting style, studying up on their strengths and weaknesses in order to develop a strategic game plan to exploit any perceived vulnerabilities to increase their chances of victory.

Unlike human athletes who can study their opponents' patterns in a video analysis room, predators in the wild, such as the coyote, must learn these skills through direct experience in their natural environment. Driven by the relentless force of hunger, these creatures have no choice but to quickly adapt and develop their hunting tactics, transforming themselves into formidable hunters in the unforgiving world of nature.

post_Description:
Elegant Destruction

📽 by @thesecretlifeofconnor

Elephants, known for their incredible strength and large size, have various reasons for knocking over trees. These powerful herbivores consume a significant amount of vegetation daily, and toppling trees grants them access to otherwise unreachable leaves, twigs, bark, and uprooted tree roots. Their strength is exemplified by their versatile trunk, which contains over 40,000 muscles and can lift up to 700 pounds (approximately 317 kg). Additionally, their massive size and muscular build enable them to exert immense force when necessary.

Another reason elephants knock over trees is to create open spaces for easier movement and social interactions within their herd. These spaces also generate new habitats and food sources for other species, making elephants a keystone species in their ecosystems. Furthermore, they may push over trees to access minerals in the soil or hidden water sources beneath the roots, particularly during times of drought.

Tree-knocking can also serve as a form of communication and dominance display within the herd or to intimidate potential threats. Elephants may push against trees to scratch themselves, remove parasites, and shed old skin. To knock over large trees, they employ a combination of their body weight, trunk, and tusks, exerting a substantial amount of force.

Although tree-knocking is a natural behavior for elephants, it can lead to deforestation and habitat destruction when their population density becomes too high in a specific area.

post_Description:
Rerouting

Moose sends a dogsledding couple offroading

I don’t know enough about moose to tell you exactly what triggered this hostile response, but I have seen similar clips and if I had to guess, I would say it has everything to do with the dogs.

But why?

When we look at a dogsled, we just see sled dogs, but when moose look at a dogsled, they see a group of medium-sized canids that look an awful lot like wolves. Considering that dogs and wolves are very closely related, plus the fact that moose have evolved alongside wolves over years and years and know that they represent true existential danger, it's not really a huge stretch to say that this is an instinctual reaction to a perceived threat.

Again, I’m talking out of my butthole here. These are just my thoughts

In general, moose are not aggressive animals, but they can become defensive and dangerous if they feel threatened or cornered.

Some of you might be wondering about the status of the dogs and the people involved, and I can tell you that while everyone was understandably shaken (with the exception of the guy with the camera - he sounds like he's bored) , they all made it home unscathed.

post_Description:
Turf War

📽 by @andrediving

Moray eel and a octopus fight over a hiding spot

Looking for a place to hang out isn't always as simple as finding a spot and parking your ribbonesque anatomy inside of it. Sometimes your spot of choice is already occupied.

This is precisely what is happening here, and even though the octopus technically has dibs on this primo spot, it is the moray who wins this fight in the end - tearing the tenacious octopus’ arm off and eating it for good measure.

Not to worry: When an octopus loses one of its arms, it has the amazing ability to grow it back by regenerating the tissue. After the arm is lost, special cells at the injury site, called blastema cells, start to multiply and form a small lump. These cells act like a construction crew, working together to rebuild the missing arm.

The blastema cells transform into different types of cells that make up the new arm, such as muscle cells, nerve cells, and skin cells. This process is guided by signals in the octopus's body that tell the cells where to go and what to become. It takes some time for the arm to fully regrow, and although the new limb might look just like the original, it may not be as strong or flexible.

This process of tissue regeneration does require a significant amount of energy. The octopus must allocate resources, such as proteins, fats, and sugars to fuel the growth and development of the new limb. This energy is used by the blastema cells to multiply, differentiate into various cell types, and ultimately rebuild the lost structure.

During the regrowth process, the octopus might need to consume more food to meet its increased energy demands. Despite the energy expenditure, the ability to regrow a limb provides the octopus with a significant survival advantage in its challenging marine environment.

post_Description:
Just The Tip

Raccoon takes advantage of a cold stunned iguana

When the temperature drops below 50°F (10°C), iguanas, which are cold-blooded reptiles, can become "cold stunned". This is a physiological response in which their body temperature drops and they become immobile or sluggish. In extreme cases, they may appear dead.

Cold stunned iguanas are relatively common in Florida, where these lizards have been introduced and are not native to the environment. During cold snaps, iguanas may fall from trees or become immobilized on the ground. They are not necessarily dead, but they may be in a state of shock.

As a defense mechanism to evade predators, iguanas have the ability to detach their tails. Because this part of their body is considered “expendable” the nerve endings in their tails are not as sensitive as within the rest of their body. This reduced sensitivity allows them to take tail damage without stressing as much about it.

Not saying the iguana can’t feel this, but the combination of cold stun and reduced sensitivity in the tail might be the reason the iguana looks like he can't be bothered in response to being gnawed on by this trash panda.

post_Description:
Body Shots

📽 by @pacificoffshore

“Orcas rarely use their teeth to kill prey. Most of the time a combination of body-slamming, head-butting and slaps from the tail are used to inflict blunt force trauma. While this is no doubt a sad video in some respects, this is the way of the Orca. One dolphin fed the entire pod of five for at least one whole day.” - Ryan Lawler

Orcas are the largest members of the dolphin family, so while larger “killer whale” dolphins killing and eating a smaller member of their extended family might seem strange, and some might be tempted to call this behavior cannibalistic, it is normal behavior and definitely not cannibalism.

Cannibalistic behavior refers to the act of consuming the flesh or organs belonging to a member of your own species. If a human eats a human, that's cannibalism. If a killer whale eats another killer whale, that's cannibalism. Members of the same taxonomic rank consuming each other is not considered cannibalism because even though they are classified within the same “family” they are different species.

post_Description:
POLLO E PATATE IN PADELLA
Pochi ingredienti e una ricetta semplice per un secondo saporito e sostanzioso, perfetto anche come piatto unico per una cenetta in famiglia 😘

INGREDIENTI

1,2kg pollo in pezzi
1,2kg patate
1/2 bicchiere vino bianco
4 spicchi aglio
rosmarino fresco q.b.
olio extravergine d’oliva q.b.
sale fino q.b.

PROCEDIMENTO

In un tegame bello capiente mettiamo un po’ d’olio e sistemiamo il pollo, cercando di non sovrapporre i pezzi. Mettiamo anche dei rametti di rosmarino e due spicchi d’aglio interi e vestiti. Accendiamo il fornello e facciamo rosolare bene la carne, girandola dopo qualche minuto per far dorare entrambi i lati poi sfumiamo con  il vino bianco. Una volta evaporato il vino, chiudiamo con il coperchio e facciamo cuocere per una mezz’ora circa, mescolando di tanto in tanto.
Mentre il pollo cuoce, occupiamoci delle patate: peliamole, laviamole e tagliamole a cubetti di medie dimensioni.
Quando il pollo è quasi cotto, aggiustiamo di sale e lasciamo il coperchio a soffietto per far evaporare un po’ del liquido di cottura e far rosolare la carne a puntino. Una volta ben rosolato il pollo, spegniamo e togliamolo dal tegame mettendolo da parte (togliamo anche l’aglio e il rosmarino).
Nello stesso tegame mettiamo le patate, poi aggiungiamo un po’ di rosmarino (questa volta spezzettato) e due spicchi d’aglio a pezzetti. Riaccendiamo il fuoco, diamo una bella mescolata e facciamo cuocere per circa 15 minuti, dopo aver aggiustato di sale e coperto con il coperchio. Quando sono pronte le patate, rimettiamo in pentola anche il pollo, mescoliamo e lasciamo insaporire tutto insieme per 3-4 minuti.
Pronto! Portiamo in tavola il nostro pollo e patate in padella bello fumante e… buon appetito!

post_Description:
SEPPIE RIPIENE AL FORNO
Un secondo piatto facile da preparare, leggero e perfetto per un pranzo o una cenetta a base di pesce 😊

INGREDIENTI
4 seppie (pulite)
150g piselli freschi o surgelati
1/2 cipolla
1 carota
100g pomodori pachino
pangrattato q.b.
olio extravergine d’oliva q.b.
sale fino q.b.

PROCEDIMENTO
In una padella facciamo soffriggere in un po’ di olio la carota e la cipolla tritate. Aggiungiamo i piselli e facciamo cuocere per qualche minuto. Uniamo anche i pomodorini tagliati a spicchi, aggiustiamo di sale e ultimiamo la cottura.
Sistemiamo le seppie pulite in una teglia rivestita di carta forno e farciamole con il sughetto di piselli e pomodorini. Spolveriamole con il pangrattato e irroriamole con l’olio. Mettiamo a cuocere in forno preriscaldato ventilato a 180°C per circa 30 minuti, oppure a 190°C in forno statico per lo stesso tempo.
Ed ecco le nostre squisite seppie ripiene al forno. Buon appetito!

post_Description:
GNOCCHI DI ZUCCHINE
Una variante dei classici gnocchi, facili da fare e versatili 😘

INGREDIENTI

250g zucchine
250g ricotta
1 uovo
1 cucchiaio formaggio grattugiato
250g farina 00
noce moscata q.b.
sale fino q.b.

PROCEDIMENTO

Iniziamo a preparare i nostri gnocchi di zucchine grattugiando in una ciotola la zucchina. Saliamo e lasciamola insaporire qualche minuto.
Nel frattempo, in un’altra ciotola mettiamo la ricotta, l’uovo, il formaggio grattugiato, un pizzico di sale e un po’ di noce moscata. Amalgamiamo bene tutto con una forchetta. Aggiungiamo le zucchine ben strizzate, in modo da eliminare tutta l’acqua che avranno rilasciato, e mescoliamo. Iniziamo ad aggiungere la farina, un po’ alla volta e continuando a mescolare. Quando l’impasto prende consistenza, continuiamo a lavorarlo sul piano, aggiungendo ancora un po’ di farina se necessario.
Una volta pronto l’impasto (dovrà essere omogeneo e morbido ma non troppo appiccicoso) stendiamolo leggermente con il mattarello. Con un coltello tagliamolo in tante strisce e poi arrotondiamole con le mani. Tagliamo le “code” ottenute in tanti pezzetti, per dar forma agli gnocchi.
Lessiamo gli gnocchi in acqua bollente salata. Scoliamoli dopo pochi minuti, non appena tornano a galla. Poi condiamo i nostri gnocchi di zucchine come più preferiamo e portiamoli in tavola belli fumanti! Possiamo farli burro e salvia: un condimento classico, delicato e profumato. Oppure conditi con una deliziosa cremina allo zafferano: un gusto ricco e avvolgente! O ancora nel modo forse più tradizionale: con un un bel sughetto di pomodori e basilico! Un primo perfetto per il pranzo della domenica in famiglia.

post_Description:
PASTA BISCOTTO PERFETTA, vi assicuro che è infallibile, è soffice e super elastica, in questo modo quando la arrotolerete non si romperà! ❤️

INGREDIENTI

5 uova
70 g zucchero
70 g olio di semi
50 g farina oppure amido di mais
La scorza grattugiata di 1 limone

PROCEDIMENTO

Per prima cosa prendiamo due ciotole e dividiamo i tuorli dagli albumi. Iniziamo con l’aiuto delle fruste elettriche a montare gli albumi a neve, aggiungiamo lo zucchero poco alla volta e montiamo bene fino a quando non si sarà ben amalgamato.
Incorporiamo i tuorli uno alla volta e continuiamo a mescolare con l’aiuto delle fruste.
A questo punto aggiungiamo la scorza di un limone e mescoliamo.
Uniamo con l’aiuto di una frusta l’olio di semi poco alla volta.
Versiamo la farina (o l’amido di mais) setacciata e amalgamiamo bene delicatamente.
Rivestiamo una teglia da 35 x 35 cm oppure una placca da forno con carta forno e versiamo all’interno.
Con l’aiuto di una spatola livelliamolo bene. Inforniamo a 180 °C per 13-15 minuti in forno statico, oppure a 170 °C per 13-15 minuti in forno ventilato. Una volta pronto, sforniamo e lasciamolo raffreddare qualche minuto, rovesciamo la base su un foglio di carta forno pulito e delicatamente rimuoviamo il foglio usato in cottura. Lasciamo raffreddare completamente il rotolo prima di farcirlo e arrotolarlo!

post_Description:
MUFFIN DI PASQUA ARANCIA E CIOCCOLATO 🐣
Una ricetta semplicissima e veloce per dei muffin con arancia e cioccolato golosi e pratici, perfetti da portare con noi nelle gite di Pasquetta 😘
Video ricetta in collaborazione con @paneangeliofficial

INGREDIENTI
3 uova
150g zucchero
1 arancia (scorza grattugiata)
1 filetta Aroma Arancia Paneangeli
120g olio di semi
120g succo d’arancia
270g farina
1 bustina lievito per dolci Pane degli Angeli Paneangeli
70g Arancia candita Paneangeli
80g Gocce di Cioccolato Paneangeli

PROCEDIMENTO
In una ciotola rompiamo le uova e aggiungiamo lo zucchero.
Grattugiamo nella ciotola la scorza d’arancia e aggiungiamo la fialetta di
Aroma Arancia Paneangeli.
Spremiamo il succo dell’arancia sino a ottenerne circa 120 grammi e teniamolo da parte.
Iniziamo a frullare le uova e gli altri ingredienti fino a ottenere un composto chiaro e gonfio.
A questo punto aggiungiamo l’olio di semi e frulliamo ancora.
Versiamo nella ciotola il succo dell’arancia e mescoliamo per amalgamarlo.
Sempre frullando, iniziamo a incorporare la farina un po’ alla volta.
Uniamo anche il lievito per dolci Pane degli Angeli Paneangeli.
Aggiungiamo ora le Gocce di Cioccolato Paneangeli e l’Arancia candita Paneangeli e mescoliamo con una spatola per distribuirle nell’impasto.
Una volta amalgamati tutti gli ingredienti, suddividiamo l’impasto in uno stampo per muffin da 12 con i pirottini inseriti (se lo abbiamo, aiutiamoci con un porzionatore da gelato).
Cuociamo le nostre tortine in forno preriscaldato ventilato a 170°C per 25 minuti, o in forno statico a 180°C per lo stesso tempo.
Sforniamoli, lasciamoli intiepidire un po’ e poi gustiamo i nostri deliziosi muffin arancia e cioccolato!

post_Description:
FUSILLI CON SALMONE, RICOTTA E LIMONE un primo piatto cremoso e saporito, pronto in pochi minuti ❤️

INGREDIENTI
320g fusilli o altra pasta
200g salmone affumicato
250g ricotta
1 scalogno
La scorza grattugiata di 1 limone
Olio extravergine di oliva q.b.
Sale fino q.b.
erba cipollina per decorare q.b.

PROCEDIMENTO

Mettiamo subito a cuocere la pasta in acqua bollente salata. Intanto prepariamo il condimento: in una padella mettiamo un filo d’olio, lo scalogno tritato e facciamo soffriggere.
Spezzettiamo il salmone direttamente in padella e facciamolo rosolare giusto un paio di minuti.
Uniamo la ricotta, aggiungiamo un mestolo di acqua di cottura della pasta e facciamo sciogliere la ricotta, amalgamando bene.
Grattugiamo nel condimento abbondante scorza di limone e poi aggiustiamo di sale. Scoliamo la pasta al dente direttamente in padella e diamo una bella mescolata.
Impiattiamo la nostra pasta ricotta e salmone e, se ci va, decoriamo con dell’erba cipollina tritata. Buon appetito!

Padang (ANTARA) @antaranewscom -
Gubernur Sumatera Barat, Mahyeldi menilai film Buya Hamka sarat akan teladan, terutama bagi generasi muda tentang bagaimana cara memadupadankan agama, budaya dan ilmu ke dalam karakter pribadi untuk mencapai aktualisasi diri.

"Dalam film tersebut, kita disuguhi bagaimana sosok Buya Hamka menerapkan pemahaman agama, budaya dan ilmu ke dalam karakternya untuk menjadi pribadi yang dihormati dan disegani," katanya di Padang, Sabtu.
 
Ia menyebutkan bahwa tidak banyak orang yang memiliki karakter seperti Buya Hamka, yang dikenal sebagai seorang ulama, penulis, filsuf, pengajar, cendekiawan dan politikus.
 
"Sangat pantas rasanya, jika sosoknya menjadi teladan bagi banyak orang. Buya Hamka adalah inspirasi dan teladan yang maafnya tidak bertepi, toleransinya tak tertandingi dan ilmunya seluas bumi," katanya.
 
Ia mengajak masyarakat "Minang", terutama generasi muda untuk beramai-ramai menonton film Buya Hamka pada bulan April nanti.
 
"Saya berharap, masyarakat Sumbar dapat beramai-ramai menonton film ini nantinya. Jadilah kisah perjuangan Buya Hamka tersebut sebagai inspirasi kita semua," kata Mahyeldi.

post_Description:
“Sorry I'm not home right now
I'm walking into spiderwebs
So leave a message
And I'll call you back.” 🎶

A likely story, no doubt. Our favorite part of spring is walking into spider webs and screaming every time. What’s yours?

We’ve all walked through a web. Here’s a few tips to get through it. Well, you already went through it, but we digress. Here’s some tips.

🕸️ As you walk down a trail, use a stick to make first contact with potential webs, unless you prefer using your face. Do what feels right.

🕸️ Sleep in and let the early risers clear the trail for you. Or bring a (We’re not going to say it. Rhymes with wall) friend with you and put them up front.

🕸️ Keep in mind the average spider can spin or repair a web in about 30 to 60 minutes. Something to consider if the trail is a loop and you’re doing laps or if you’re feeling guilty for ruining the spider’s day. How could you?

Image: A spider web covered with morning dew drops at @theodorerooseveltnps. NPS/A. Myran

post_Description:
“I'm so glad we're doing this…Also, I've been neglecting my wellness journey, so the cherry blossoms opening when we both have time off is really ticking a lot of boxes for me.” - David Rose

Just in time for the weekend, cherry trees in Washington DC have reached peak bloom! The blooming of the cherry trees around the Tidal Basin has come to symbolize the natural beauty of our nation's capital city. The famous trees, a gift of Japan in 1912, signal Washington's beginning of spring with an explosion of life and color that surrounds the Tidal Basin in a sea of pale pink and white blossoms.

You can help us preserve cherry trees! Protecting trees happens at the roots, branches, and blossoms. Leaving blossoms on the trees - even on the ground! - is critical for the tree's interactions with pollinators like bees. Being gentle with the branches by not swinging or climbing keeps the trees strong and whole. Walking around roots keeps the soil loose enough for water to absorb, and protects the tree's roots.

Check out the BloomCam and plan your visit to @nationalmallnps at www.nps.gov/cherry 🌸

Big, if true.

Oh, it’s big and true. Some might even say tree-mendous! From a seed no bigger than one from a tomato, California's coast redwood (Sequoia sempervirens) can grow to a height of 367 feet (112 m) and have a width of 22 feet (7 m) at its base. The species is the tallest, among the oldest, and one of the most massive tree species on Earth. In fact, the trees can reach ages of 2,000 years and regularly reach 600 years.

Spring has sprung!

In the Northern Hemisphere, the March equinox (aka spring equinox or vernal equinox) occurs when the Sun crosses the equator line, heading north. This event marks the start of spring in the northern half of the globe. It’s a season of renewal and change, a time of rebirth often bringing warmer temperatures, new life, and splashes of color all across nature. Though it may not feel or look like spring in all the parks quite yet, it’s never too early to start planning your next park adventure or finding a place to venture outdoors.

Also known as Wednesday. Hey there, wolverine. Where you headed? The wolverine is very quick and can run at speeds of up to 30 miles per hour when chasing its prey or late for work. The wolverine is also known to store its food in caches to eat later. Those are my leftovers, Janet.

P.S. A wolverine’s front feet have long, semi-retractile claws that help it climb trees. They are not made of Adamantium.

post_Description:
Many visitors to national parks today collect passport stamps, magnets, patches, t-shirts, or other memorabilia to recall their trip and to show others where they’ve been. In the 1920s and 1930s the “must have” souvenirs weren’t created to be collected at all. National Park Service windshield stickers served a practical administrative purpose; they were evidence that the automobile license fees due at some parks had been paid. Americans embraced the stickers' colorful, artistic designs, sparking a collecting craze. Drivers pasted so many to their windshields they quickly became a safety hazard. The stickers were reduced in size and eventually phased out. After WWII, the first self-adhesive bumper stickers were created in 1946, and visitors had a new way to decorate their cars and show off where they’ve been.

Learn more about the sticker craze by clicking the link in our bio.

Image 1: A 1920 Yosemite National Park windshield sticker featuring a cougar on the front. (Courtesy of Yosemite National Park

Image 2: A 1921 Yellowstone National Park windshield sticker featuring a bison on the front. (NPS History Collection)

Image 3: Death Valley changed its sticker design in 1939, the season before the windshield stickers were eliminated. (NPS History Collection

Image 4: Some of the park windshield stickers issued in 1936. (NPS History Collection)

Image 5: The safety hazards the stickers presented can be seen in this photo from Yosemite National Park, 1922.

Keep calm and peduncle on.

Peduncle elongation, that is. It’s not funny. It’s science. During stage 4, (peduncle elongation) the cherry blossom buds begin to open and the flower petals begin to show. This means the blossoms are now two stages away from peak bloom. The bloom process happens in six stages – Green buds, florets visible, extension of florets, peduncle elongation, puffy blossom, and peak bloom. This year's forecast says peak bloom will be between March 22 - March 25. 🌸

post_Description:
I have no misconceptions about love. I have seen too many romantic movies and read too many fairytales to know that love is not a simple 'happily ever after'. i don't think that all you need is to find 'the one' and everything else will fall into place.

Honestly, I have no idea why people relate love to this magical feeling where someone is all starry-eyed and doting and neither one can do anything wrong.

Because this whole idea that love is perfection and love is calm waters is a horrible way to introduce someone to what loving you could feel like.

I'm human. I will make mistakes. And you and I are so very different. There will be times when we just simply cannot agree with one another, there will be times when one of us is wrong, and in those times what will you think about love? Will you consider yourself having fallen out of love? Because of course you will have an argument, of course there will be tears and a feeling that they don't understand you at all, so what now? do you just give up?

Because that's the kind of love we are being taught. The kind that makes you question the bad times, the kind that give you no room to be angry or make a mistake or call someone out on something they did, because if you do then according to the standards set by "romantic notions" you couldn't possibly be in love.

But you are, you know you are. and that's why all this stuff feels so wrong.

Love is supposed to be everything including the bad times, especially the bad times. Because when you love someone, really love someone, even when you fight you're always on the same team.
__

written by @artalanche_ridhigupta for The Scribbled Stories

post_Description:
it is not easy to open up. it is not a cakewalk to let someone know your depths. it might seem like conversations are easy, but finding the right person to have them with is not.

it takes courage to step out of the cage your mind has trapped you in, and it takes trust to believe that someone out there is worth stepping out for. so no matter how important it is to share, it is equally scary.

efforts decide where the mind wants to rest. efforts are valuable, it is needed, but at the same time, it is seldom appreciated. the give and take process is what confuses us all. the measurements of how much to put in and accept can cost people their relationships, friendships and peace of mind.

but we all learn, don’t we? we all grow with experience and get better with realisations. hurting and getting hurt always go hand in hand. you just have to decide what affects you more.

for once, let people make you feel valued. for once, hold back and give in to the endless possibilities that life has planned for you. for once, don’t decide how you want to see it going, but just let it flow. for once, put in your efforts in taking time to open up. for once, just for once, do what you feel like and not what you think people might like.

you decide your own worth by how you let people treat you. look out for those who truly want to stay for you.
___

written by @justmusingsandcoffee for The Scribbled Stories

post_Description:
Aku dan kamu ada dalam satu nafas dan detak
Pagi dan malamku menjadi pagi dan malammu
Waktu yang bergulir membuat kita berdua menunggu
Menunggu hari ini akan tiba masanya

Ketika aku sedih kau jadi resah
Ketika aku bahagia kau jadi tenang
Setiap gerakmu mengandung makna
Yang hanya bisa kuungkap mengapa

ini rasanya hadapi perpisahan yang bahagia
Meninggalkan hari demi hari yang terjadi sementara
Ada rasa sakit yang bisa kunikmati
Perasaan yang hanya aku dan kamu ketahui

Hari ini aku menangis dan kau menangis
Tangisan kemenangan yang hanya kita miliki
Aku mendekapmu dalam pelukan eratku
Air mata bahagiaku melihat malaikat kecilku

Kurangkai kalimat yang indah
Mensyukuri anugerah Sang Kuasa
Yang telah lama ku nantikan
Kini nyata dalam pelukan

Selamat datang ke dunia anakku “Chloe Emmanuelle Van Wattimena”

Papa dan Mama mencintaimu selamanya..

post_Description:
Perdido entre correos, revisiones, whatsapps, vídeos, llamadas, campañas… de repente te veo en mi cabeza para darme cuenta de que ya hace un mes. Un mes de esa semana. Donde una vez más, perdido entre todas esas cosas que yo consideraba importantes recibí una llamada de papá para decirme que estabas mal.
¿Pero cómo ibas a estar tu mal? Si eres la persona más fuerte que jamás he conocido. Si cada vez que te veía nadar en la playa de las lapas y salías del agua con un pulpo amarrado al brazo pensaba que eras uno de esos mutantes de los mismos cómics que me comprabas.
¿Cómo iba a estar mal el Tigre de Monte Alto del que tantas historias se contaban en la calle del faro?
¿Cómo ibas a estar mal si con tu edad subías todas esas escaleras infinitas mejor que yo?
Era imposible. Era algo que por mucho que me había planteado nunca me llegué a creer del todo. Tú no podias estar mal. Tú no me podías faltar.
Un mes. Un mes y no sé si ha sido una eternidad o apenas unos días. Has hecho que el tiempo funcione de otra manera desde que te fuiste.

Una conocida me dijo que los abuelos no se van, se vuelven invisibles. Pero yo te veo. Cierro los ojos y te veo. Te veo corriendo detrás de mi, por la Torre de Hércules, tirándonos bayas de los arbustos. Te veo detrás de mi portería, con tu paraguas negro mientras diluvia, diciéndome como tengo que tirarme para parar el balón antes de que marquen gol. Te veo mientras comemos, cambiándome mi vaso de cocacola por el tuyo de vino sin que me diese cuenta mientras yo solo tengo ojos para ver Digimon. Te veo en el parque de curros, gritándome para que no me tire con la bicicleta cuesta abajo. Te veo persiguiendo saltamontes y lagartos en la aldea, entre partida y partida a las cartas. Te veo las pasadas navidades cantándole a la abuela y contándome cómo os conocisteis. Te veo todavía por ese hueco de la escalera, por el que me mirabas con tu sonrisa cuando volvía a casa hubiesen pasado unas horas, un día o incluso meses. Te veo abuelo, te veo con esa sonrisa. Por mucho que ahora cuando vuelva a casa esa escalera esté vacía, te veo entre las estrellas y no pienso dejar de verte.
Así que nos vemos a las 8, cuando sale el tren a Pontevedra.

post_Description:
Te amo mi Maikelito, con toda mi vida, por siempre 🥺🫶🏽❤️✨ Descanza en paz. Gracias por contenerme, cuidarme y enseñarme tantas cosas valiosas con tus garritas dulces y ronroneos preciosos. Abriste todas las puertas posibles de mi corazón, y te extrañaré como nunca he extrañado a nadie. Mi guardián, mi gatito, que tus patitas sigan el camino que tú alma gatuna tiene para ti, ❤️🥺 Estoy segura nos encontraremos por ahí, y que conquistaras a todos adonde sea que hayas ido.

Porque sentimos la muerte como algo tan doloroso? Si debiese solo de agradecer tu existencia y saber que siempre sea como sea vivirás en mi. Pero me es inevitable sentir ese dolor desgarrador, y esa pena que a penas se calma.
Sé que es solo tiempo… 🥺🫶🏽❤️
Lo verdaderamente importante de la vida es disfrutar y aprovechar cada rayito de felicidad que nos entrega el destino, en presente, y así lo hice contigo, desde el primer momento, por eso sé que disfrutamos y vivimos la mejor vida juntos 🥺❤️✨ Te amo mi eterno guardián.

post_Description:
Out Of All The Things In 2022 The Best Part Was Getting Married To My Person. Not A Title But THEE Person I Need When I’m Up. When I’m Down. To Vent To. To Laugh With. To Cry On. To Smile At. To Turn Up With. To Cuddle Up With. To Argue. To Love On. To Do This Here Life With!!

All I Know Is Marriage Is NOT For The Weak! Everyday It’s A Choice To Do Right By Someone Else. To Be Selfless And To Place Someone In Your Shoes And Be Kind And Show Up To Give Them Unconditional Love. To Love Them Through Their Flaws. To Make Room For Mistakes. To Learn And Grow Together. To Remove The Pressure Of Being Perfect And Let Your Hair Down. To Trust Without Limits. To Have A Partner To Weather The Storm With While Embarking On The Beautiful Days. To Make Life Brighter and Easier For. To Continue To Pray Over And Uplift Even When Things Just Seem Outta Whack.

My Person. My Bestfriend. My Husband. MI AMOR. We Are The Same Type Of Wild But Differ In Taste Buds. @money23green You Have Changed Me From Elsa To MamaB While Still Allowing Me To Be ME. I Can’t Thank God Enough For YOU! I Love You Always💚 Look What Just Having Fun Turned Into When That Fork In The Road Came Stared At Me! Thank You To Our Family & Close Friends That Shared In & Supported Our Journey & Big Weekend! It Was Thee Littest🔥😜 #ForeverSeeingGreen #BlackLove #WeGoinBeLivingLikeThisForTheRestOfOurLIVES 💚

GEÇMİŞ OLSUN TÜRKİYEM

Acımızı tarif etmek imkansız, herkes gibi duygularımı anlatmakta zorluk çekiyorum. Kalbim afet bölgesi ile birlikte atıyor. Binlerce insan çaresizce onlara uzatılacak bir yardım eli bekliyor. Çok üzgünüm...

Depremde hayatını kaybeden vatandaşlarımıza Allah'tan rahmet, yakınlarına baş sağlığı ve yaralılarımıza acil şifalar diliyorum.

Acımız, kaybımız büyük ve şartlar çok zor…Şimdi elimizden geldiğince deprem bölgesine malzeme desteğini sağlama zamanı.

Tüm bu yardımlarla beraber doğru kaynaklardan doğru bilgileri de edinmeye ihtiyaç var. Bu durumu kolaylaştırmak için faydalı linkleri bir araya getirmeye çalıştım. Bio’daki linkten; bağışlarınızı ve desteklerinizi gerçekleştirebilir, bilgi edinebilirsiniz.

post_Description:
This is called a vietnamese pizza and I was so intrigued to try it when I learned about it from @nutritionbykylie and @myhealthydish because you only need 3 ingredients and 5 minutes. 🙌
INGREDIENTS
1 rice paper
2 teaspoons chili oil
1 egg
1 tablespoon sliced green onions or parsley
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Heat a small nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add the rice paper on the dry heated skillet.
2. Once the rice paper starts to fold up, add the chili oil and one egg. Gently scramble the egg around with the chili oil until the egg is cooked. Add sliced green onions, parsley or any other toppings like kewpie mayo and/or sriracha.
3. Fold in half and serve immediately.

post_Description:
Did you know you can make lasagna with greek yogurt? #Sponsored I use it sometimes instead of ricotta when I want something with less fat and calories or simply when I forgot to buy ricotta. 🙌 I always have @Stonyfield Greek yogurt in my fridge to use for cooking, baking and snacking. I love that it’s pesticide-free, organic and made from high-quality ingredients that I feel good about feeding to my family. #stonyfield #organic
INGREDIENTS
> For assembly
1 pound lasagna sheets
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
> Meat Sauce
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 pound lean ground beef
1 onion chopped
2 garlic cloves minced
1 28- ounce can crushed tomatoes
½ cup tomato paste
1 tablespoon Italian seasoning
1 teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon black pepper
> Greek Yogurt Sauce
1 ½ cups Stonyfield Organic Greek yogurt
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
1 cup shredded parmesan cheese
1 egg
¼ cup chopped fresh basil plus more for garnish
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon black pepper
INSTRUCTIONS
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook lasagna sheets in boiling water until al dente, for about 8 minutes. Drain the pasta, and rinse with cold water. Set aside.
To make the meat sauce, heat the olive oil over medium heat in a large deep skillet. Add the ground beef, onions and garlic, season with Italian seasoning, salt and pepper, and cook until beef is well browned, about 10 minutes. Add the crushed tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer until the sauce is thickened, 10 more minutes. Set aside.
Preheat the oven to 375˚F
In a large bowl, combine the yogurt, cheeses, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
To assemble, add 1 cup of the meat sauce to a 9x13 baking dish and spread evenly. Arrange 4 cooked lasagna sheets on top. Layer 1/3 of the Greek yogurt mixture and 1/3 of the remaining meat sauce. Continue for 2 more layers, and finish with lasagna sheets topped with the meat sauce and the remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes. Remove the foil, and bake for an additional 20 minutes or until the cheese is golden and bubbly. Let rest for 15 minutes before cutting.

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/greek-yogurt-lasagna/

post_Description:
If you like snickers, you’re going to love these date snickers made with just four ingredients. 🍫 I’m obsessed and can’t wait to make another batch of these! Inspired by @moribyan

INGREDIENTS
12 medjool dates
¼ cup peanut butter
¼ cup chopped roasted peanuts
4 ounces dark chocolate bar, cut into chunks
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Use a small sharp knife to cut a slit in each date lengthwise. Remove the pits.
2. Fill each date with 1 teaspoon peanut butter and add 1 teaspoon of crushed peanuts on top. Set aside.
3. Place the chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl. Place the bowl in the microwave at 30 second intervals. Stir chocolate in between each 30 seconds until all chocolate is melted.
4. Place a toothpick inside each stuffed date and dip the date in the melted chocolate. Use a spoon to coat the date completely in the chocolate, then allow any excess chocolate to drip off.
5. Transfer the chocolate covered date to a tray or plate lined with parchment. Sprinkle the top with the remaining crushed peanuts.
6. Place the dates in the fridge to allow the chocolate to set, about 10 minutes.

Created by Yoko Ono, "Wish Tree for Bilbao" is a participatory work inspired by the Japanese tradition of hanging prayers from a shrub, tree, or bamboo plant.

As part of a series she began in 1996, Ono invites visitors to write their wishes for peace. After being hung on the tree, they are sent to her to be included in her project "Imagine Peace Tower," an environmental light installation located in an open landscape on Viðey Island, Reykjavík, Iceland, created in memory of her late husband, John Lennon.

This work is on view at @museoguggenheim.
___
Pictured: Yoko Ono, "Wish Tree for Bilbao," 1996/2014. #YokoOno #GuggenheimWomensHistory

post_Description:
"Since my childhood, I have always made works with polka dots. Earth, moon, sun and human beings all represent dots; a single particle among billions." —Yayoi Kusama

Happy birthday to Yayoi Kusama, born in 1929 in Matsumoto, Nagano Prefecture, Japan!

After arriving in New York in June 1958, Kusama began a series of patterned monochrome paintings called "Infinity Nets." She filled the canvases with small, arched paint strokes that emerged as specks and dots.

Kusama has said that the dots reflect her desire to "predict and measure the infinity of the unbounded universe, from my own position in it." She also imbued the works with psychological content, describing them as realizations of a hallucination of being suffocated by nets.

⚪️🎨: Yayoi Kusama, "No. 2. J.B.," 1960. © Yayoi Kusama. #YayoiKusama

post_Description:
Although James Rosenquist avoids storytelling and explicit narrative, his paintings are full of meaning. Like a good poem, a Rosenquist painting asks you to seek out information.

The fragmented images and strange juxtapositions of objects serve to increase the possibilities for multiple meanings and levels of interpretation. The abrupt color changes and scale disrupt the process of recognition and are filled with contradictions that suggest metaphors rather than specific stories.

Like complex poetry, Rosenquist’s paintings require time. Unlike advertising images, they cannot be taken in at a glance.
___
Pictured: James Rosenquist, "The Swimmer in the Econo-mist (painting 3)," 1997-98. © James Rosenquist. #JamesRosequist #WorldPoetryDay

post_Description:
Ana Mendieta's work revolves around the body, nature, and spiritual connections between them. A Cuban exile, Mendieta came to the United States in 1961, leaving much of her family behind—a traumatic cultural separation that impacted her art.

Her Silueta series (begun in 1973) used a typology of abstracted feminine forms through which she hoped to access an "omnipresent female force." Working in Iowa and Mexico, she carved and shaped her figure into the earth, with arms overhead to represent the merger of earth and sky, floating in the water to symbolize the minimal space between land and sea, or with arms raised and legs together to signify a wandering soul.
___
Pictured: Ana Mendieta, "Silueta Muerta," 1976. © Ana Mendieta. #AnaMendieta #GuggenheimWomensHistory

post_Description:
Hoy nace mi niño, y con él una tía.

Estas a punto de nacer y ya me has convertido en alguien muy poderosa. Esperarte, soñarte e imaginarte ha sido un bálsamo para este mundo loco al que llegas hoy.
Lo siento, no es un mundo perfecto, como tampoco lo fue cuando nacimos tu papá y yo, pero era un poquito menos peor de lo que es ahora. No pudimos hacer nada al respecto mi niño pero estoy segura que a pesar de eso, serás feliz.
Te dedico todas las canciones de amor que existan, las que traigan alguna palabra con tía serán para ti: telepaTÍA, empaTÍA, valenTÍA y hasta homeopaTÍA…!
Que el mundo hostil al que llegas te reciba y te mantenga amigablemente: que la oscuridad que encuentres en el camino solo sirva para contrastar la luz con la que siempre alumbrarás.
Yo te deseo una vida plena, llena de aspavientos y contradicciones; una vida austera, que te permita el poder de la libertad. Sé libre mi niño, sé gentil y generoso, date ese lujo. Quiero que tengas una vida de privilegios: el privilegio de la risa, las buenas compañías, los intensos amores, la inconsciencia de la buena salud, la certeza de los gritos y la buena ventura de tus luchas. Sé un buen ser humano para este alocado mundo q no parará de sorprenderte muchas veces para bien e inevitablemente para mal. Que el amor te sobre tanto que puedas compartirlo; que puedas reparar corazones rotos y que tu corazón roto siempre encuentre reparo. Que tu faro sea la coherencia y el desenfado; que heredes de nosotros las ganas de permanecer juntos y reírnos de nada. Hoy el mundo es un lugar mejor porque existes. Hagas lo que hagas, yo siempre estaré para ti, porque eres mi niño, porque soy tu tía desde hoy y para siempre. Gracias por ese regalo.

Three TikTok users said they believe their video was the inspiration for thousands of people to troll Truth Social, the social media platform launched by former President Trump.

Teresa Williams thought she had landed her dream job in Iron Mountain, Michigan, becoming the first female officer in the history of the rural town's police department.

But she was relentlessly harassed and assaulted during her 4½ years there and ultimately resigned, according to a federal lawsuit she filed last month against three Iron Mountain officers.

Within weeks of being hired in 2017, she was forced to make out with her direct supervisor at a bar, according to the suit. The supervisor and Williams’ former patrol partner also bet on who could have sex with her first, the suit says.

“Just because you wear a badge and you’re a cop, it doesn’t mean you’re above the law. It doesn’t mean you get to treat people however you want and break the law and do whatever you want,” she said.

post_Description:
A majority of Black women say they feel they have to change their hair just to be taken seriously for job opportunities and in professional settings, according to a survey commissioned by LinkedIn and Dove.

Some 66% of them said they had changed their hair for a job interview to lessen the chances of being passed over due to hair discrimination.

When looking at the data, said Andrew McCaskill, a senior director of global communications and career expert for LinkedIn, workplaces need “to work better” for women in general, but especially Black women.

Once they have landed their jobs, Black women with textured hair are twice as likely to experience microaggressions in the workplace compared to Black women with straight hair.

And 25% of Black women ages 25 to 34 surveyed said they were sent home from work because of their hair.

post_Description:
Three people have died, and four others have had their eyeballs removed because of rare bacterial infections linked to contaminated eyedrops, according to the CDC.

The agency has identified 68 patients in 16 states with Pseudomonas aeruginosa, a type of bacterium resistant to most antibiotics. Eight patients have lost vision in at least one of their eyes. Some have had to undergo corneal transplants.

Most said they had used a variety of eyedrops before becoming ill, but EzriCare Artificial Tears was most commonly reported. Those drops have since been recalled, along with Delsam Pharma's Artificial Tears and its Artificial Eye Ointment.

post_Description: ⚠️ HELMETS SAVE LIVES ⚠️ Scary story : We we’re at a friends house on Sunday having dinner together and Manilla was playing on the driveway with the other kids. They came running in yelling “Manilla is hurt!”. He had fallen off a skateboard. We ran outside and Manilla was motionless facedown on the driveway. Garrett carefully rolled him over. His eyes were open but he wasn’t moving or talking. Garrett kept asking Manilla to hold his hand but no response or movement. Our friends rushed to their other neighbor, an ER Doctor who just got home from work and was still in his scrubs. After about 30 seconds Manilla finally reached and grabbed Garrett’s hand, moved his feet, and began to speak saying “My brain hurts.” 😖💔😢 The doctor did a full assessment and Manilla got a concussion. He is doing well now and under close watch. It was one of the scariest moments of our lives. We are grateful for doctors, grateful for helmets, and SO GRATEFUL OUR MANILLA IS OKAY. 🙏🏽❤️🙏🏻

post_Description:
The project of the house of the Alférez Gorge takes its origin from the concept of a cabin and the romantic idea of a protective shelter in the middle of the forest; an isolated house seeking to resemble an object that would have been deposited on the ground, among the trees.

The configuration is developed in semi-levels around a double height, with high windows and skylights on the roof. The high volume of its double height allows to distribute the light in all interior spaces, and compensate for the loss of windows on the first floor that protects us from any intrusion.

#architecture: Ludwig Godefroy Architecture @ludwiggodefroy
#photography: Rory Gardiner @arorygardiner

A moonshot for affordable housing is here. ICON, the global leader in construction-scale 3D printing, has launched Initiative 99, a global architecture competition to reimagine affordable housing. With a $1M prize fund, architects, designers and dreamers are called to help design accessible, beautiful and dignified homes that can be built for under $99k. Registration for the competition opens in the summer of 2023 and architects from all over the world including firms, individuals, and university students are encouraged to participate. The International Call for Ideas @restore_to_impact — The next healthcare landmark for innovation and future-oriented competencies aspires to solicit innovative, evolutionary, transversal ideas to anticipate the urban/architectural redevelopment project for the regeneration of the Chiesi historical industrial site in via Palermo, Parma (Italy).

The Company has a twofold objective: to create an innovative business playground (Centre for Open Innovation & Competence) and to provide its commercial affiliate (the Italian one) with a workspace aligned to current notions of inclusion and corporate guidelines. To transform the Via Palermo site in a driver for urban regeneration and a landmark of innovation.

The Call for Ideas runs though 30 April 2023.

post_Description:
Thanks to the frameless sliding doors by @skyframe_global, the Haus am Vierwaldstättersee offers a stunning panoramic view of Lake Lucerne and the Swiss Alps. Ludwig Mies van der Rohe inspired the building owner, who wanted as few walls as possible to create an unbounded spatial experience with spectacular vistas. Today, the entire front can be opened - each nine metres wide. "For me, it's like sitting in a convertible," says the owner. The minimalist furnishings with a few noble design pieces further enhance the impression of openness and lightness.

Sky-Frame windows create an unbounded spatial experience with spectacular vistas | Sky-Frames pure appearance sides with the distinct design language of Mies van der Rohe

A GLÓRIA ETERNA 🏆

No terceiro episódio da série ZICO 70, relembramos a conquista da Taça Libertadores da América em 1981.

Com jogos emocionantes e muito disputados, o nosso craque e seus companheiros precisaram ir além da técnica pra trazer o primeiro título continental para a Gávea.

post_Description:
The stoneware piece 'Shallow Dish' by Ewen Henderson is part of a curated selection of artworks at the newly-opened CASA LOEWE Dubai presented alongside our latest collections.

Henderson is an important figure in British art and culture known for his radicalisation of ceramics and free approach to creating without formulas or methodologies.

Henderson defied typical stylistic categorisations of classic vases or tea bowls, choosing instead to fuse multiple types of clays, glazes, and stains. This often ensued with a unique patchwork, as shown in the piece at CASA LOEWE Dubai. Moving away from the wheel, Henderson preferred using his hands to achieve unique forms that pushed everyday utilitarian objects into abstractions. Often exploring the visual connection between landscape and ceramics, his works like Shallow Dish result as ancient looking artefacts, a sort of contemporary relic built of clay, one of the oldest of earth’s materials yet played with by a modern artist.

Ewen Henderson
Shallow Dish, stoneware

Dubai Mall, Fashion Avenue, Ground Floor

#LOEWE
#LOEWEdubai

post_Description:
The tapestry 'White Horse' by John Allen is part of a curated selection of artworks at the newly-opened CASA LOEWE Dubai presented alongside our latest collections.

Allen is a British artist known for his richly hued tapestries of abstracted landscapes. His bright colourful vistas offer vibrant views knitted through meticulous craftsmanship. Having collaborated with Jonathan Anderson for a LOEWE collection in 2016, his work continues to decorate LOEWE stores worldwide with his bold, colourful images that have been reproduced onto handmade wool carpets by Spanish artisans.

At CASA LOEWE Dubai, this original tapestry unites the floor pieces, richly hued ceramic walls, and colourful objects curated across the space while exhibiting high craft as high art.

John Allen
White Horse, Hand spun and dyed woven wool

Dubai Mall, Fashion Avenue, Ground Floor

#LOEWE
#LOEWEdubai

post_Description:
The sculpture 'TRIBOLOGICAL INFORMANT' by Matthew Ronay is part of a curated selection of artworks at the newly-opened CASA LOEWE Dubai presented alongside our latest collections.

At first glance, the abstract and colourful sculptures of the New York-based artist nostalgically wink at us—recalling a sort of childlike playfulness—a fusion of toy, pet, and playdoh. Yet, upon closer introspection, Ronay's artwork presents a deeper reality, drawing on various artistic influences spanning surrealism, folk-art, and mythology. A hybrid aesthetic fuses past and present, ensuing as ancient artefact and also futuristic token. Exploring the power of material objects and our relationship to them, the sculpture mimics anatomical parts, allowing the viewer to consider their body in relationship to both art and the corporeal struggle they encounter in the world. Intimate in scale and exuberant in colour, the hand-bag sized sculpture unites various forms and colours within the space.

Matthew Ronay
TRIBOLOGICAL INFORMANT, basswood, dye, gouache, flocking, plastic, steel
2018

Dubai Mall, Fashion Avenue, Ground Floor

آقای رئیس جمهور!
من نه به بیت‌المال دست درازی کردم،
نه از جایی حقوق میگیرم،
نه فسادی دارم و نه غیره!
ترتیبی بدید بعد از اعتراض برای توضیح پاره‌ای از مسائل با من تماس گرفته نشه؛ چون اصلا مساله‌ای وجود نداره غیر از اینکه من مثل همه‌ی مردم
از اختلاس، دزدی، تخلف،رانت، تبعیض، تمامیت خواهی، تنفر پراکنی بین المللی، خشونت دولتی، شعارهای توخالی هزینه زا، لاف زنی مسئولان، مشکلات کار و تولید و ...
خسته هستم!
منتظر جواب شما هستم.

Reposted @aerosmith #AeroHistory: March 22nd, 1977 Aerosmith releases the single ‘Back in the Saddle’.

A real bullwhip was intended to be used for the whip effects and hours were spent trying to get it to crack. The band members ended up cut up and hurt without making any progress. Eventually, the band decided the whip effects would be created by whirling a 30-foot cord from the studio, then by firing a cap gun to create the crack of the whip. When the song is performed in concert, Tyler often makes more noticeable lyrical and visible references to sex. Although the lyrics, by Tyler, were written with the simple idea of cowboys and sex, this song took on new meaning after Aerosmith reunited in 1984 and embarked on their ‘Back in the Saddle Tour’.

Today, the song remains a staple on classic rock radio and in concert. It is arguably one of the heaviest songs of Aerosmith’s Top 40 singles, and is cited by rock musicians @slash and James Hetfield of @metallica as among their favorite rock songs.

🎥: Back in the Saddle - Live at the Summit, Houston, TX, June 25th 1977

post_Description:
Reposted @lordrarerock HAIL, WHAT’S THE MATTER WITH YOUR MIND - Redbone perform “Come and Get Your Love” live in 1974. Of thousands of acts that earned hits in the 1970s, one stands apart for all others for a unique accomplishment. Redbone, which scored a pop hit in the U.S. in 1974 with “Come and Get Your Love,” were the first Native American band to achieve a Top 5 single on the Hot 100. Redbone had taken its name from a Cajun term for multi-racial individuals or culture and the members of Redbone drew from Yaqui, Shoshone, and Mexican heritage as well with roots in Texas, Louisiana and California. The group’s core musicians, brothers Patrick and Candido “Lolly” Vasquez-Vegas, were born in Coalinga, Calif. (near Fresno), moved to Los Angeles in 1959 and performed for a decade on the club scene as Pat and Lolly Vegas before founding Redbone. Their guitarist, pianist and vocalist was Robert Anthony Avila, though he went by the stage name Tony Bellamy.

When “Come and Get Your Love” was released as a single on Epic Records in January 1974, a longer version had been previously available on the group’s fifth studio album, 1973’s Wovoka. The genre-defying group’s multi-cultural musical blend of swamp funk, Tex-Mex, R&B, soul, Native American tribal heartbeats, hummable melodies, gelled into a pure pop masterpiece. (When the song peaked on April 13, 1974, other singles in the Top 10 included Blue Swede’s cover of “Hooked on a Feeling,” Elton John’s “Bennie and the Jets,” and John Denver’s “Sunshine on My Shoulders.”)

The single was certified RIAA platinum, signifying sales of a million copies and entered the pantheon of perennial pop radio standards and classics. Enjoy iiii]; )'

post_Description:
Reposted @lordrarerock IT AIN’T ME - Recently unearthed footage of Creedence Clearwater Revival’s storming set at Royal Albert Hall in London - 1970. This footage was initially thought to be long lost, however, it was recently uncovered and is being released in its entirety. CCR’s show at RAH is the stuff of legend. This night captured the California band just as their creativity and popularity were peaking. Much of John Fogerty’s songwriting resonated heavily with disaffected youth and their popularity was skyrocketing with the success of the album “Green River,” which was released the previous year. This amazing footage is a special as it’s the only concert footage of the original CCR lineup in its entirety.

This is an antiestablishment song of defiance and blue-collar pride, both anti-Washington and against the Vietnam War. John Fogerty and Doug Clifford both enlisted in the Army Reserves in 1966 (to avoid being drafted and shipped to Vietnam) and were discharged in 1968 after serving their military commitments. “The song speaks more to the unfairness of class than war itself,” Fogerty said. “It’s the old saying about rich men making war and poor men having to fight them.”

This is one of those songs that came together very quickly. Fogerty recalled to American Songwriter magazine in January 2013: “When I felt it was about ready to hatch, I went into my bedroom and just sat down to write. The whole thing happened in about 20 minutes. That just poured out.” Enjoy

Reposted @stanwinstonschool Pumpkinhead - From Concept to Creation - Stan Winston's Directorial Debut.

Stan Winston made his directorial debut with PUMPKINHEAD, a low-budget horror film about a man, Ed Harley (Lance Henriksen), who conjures a mythical demon to avenge the death of his son. Originally, producers from the DeLaurentiis Entertainment Group (DEG), the film's production company, had sent Winston the script hoping to engage Stan Winston Studio to create the 'Pumpkinhead' demon. But Winston quickly recognized that, in Pumpkinhead, he had found an ideal property for his film directing debut. "It was a small picture, something I thought I could handle as a director; and I felt there was a lot that I could bring to the story. So I told the producers, 'Yeah, I'll do the creature — but only if I can direct the movie.'"

post_Description:
Meet Katmai the sea otter. 🦦🧊
"Well...as long as she is doing it with ice" is a common catch phrase when watching Katmai.
Video by: @rnaqua
.
Sea otters are very well known for the fact that they are one of the few species that have learned to use tools. Most often Sea otters will utilize rocks to crack open their prey and have even been known to carry a rock in their pocket.

Researchers have studied Sea otters focusing on this skill and have discovered that there is a variety of tool use across and within Sea otter populations. The amount of tool use is very dependent on ecological factors like what kind of prey is around, but it was also noted that it was influenced by individuals learning to use tools. Aka if Katmai learns something fun like she can use a tool to break something, the likelihood of all the others learning it grows 😂
.
Info from @rnaqua & "Variation in the frequency of tool use across and within otter populations"  Jessica A Perry

Önümüzdeki hafta muazzam bir proje açıklayacağız.

250 nin üzerinde fatura var ve hepsi denetimden geçti. Yakında da İçişleri Bakanlığı denetimine sunulacak.

4) Bu 1 milyar TL ile neler yaptık?
Videoda görebilirsiniz.

Ahbap depolarından gün be gün ihtiyaç olan şehirlere sevkiyat yapılmaktadır.

İrsaliyesinden teslim tutanağına kadar evraklarımız mevcut🙏

Para Lizy su vida fue una cadena de oportunidades, así lo dijo hoy cuando dio: el SÍ.
Pero para reconocer una oportunidad y explotarla es necesario inteligencia talento, empatía, astucia y bravura.
Todo eso es Lizy.
Una mujer que por su simpatía, entró por un tubo al medio, y se convirtió en una estrella única.
De peluquera de famosas, a los escenarios KM0, de ahí a la radio, y luego a la tele. Obviamente, atravesó prejuicios, miradas, comentarios y todo lo habitual. Nada la detuvo.

La vida le robó a los papás, a su hermana elegida La Flopy (hoy estaría radiante) pero la abrió la puerta a un gran amor: el de su marido, el de sus amigos y el de público.

post_Description:
Pleno 2000, un día que me llamó para felicitarme por La Linterna, y al día siguiente para reclamarme una info negativa para con Sábado Bus! Jajajaja! Esa mini discusión de dos tercos, terminó en una amistad de quince años.
Debatíamos todo el tiempo sobre la tele y la radio, intercambiábamos información por ideas de invitados y secciones. Nos escuchábamos todo el tiempo por teléfono. Después pasamos a eternos cafés y luego a cenas con Carmela. Amaba la charla, el Morfi y los encuentros.
Cuando se separaron, las charlas incorporamos un tema: su destino amoroso. En un momento, le gustaba una de las actrices más talentosas y lindas del pais. “Queres ver como me la levantó?” Me canchereó en in Martín Fierro. Y tuvo éxito! Creo que los tres guardamos el secreto.
Éxito como en La Pregunta Animal o Gracias por venir, sus discusiones radiales, y sus programas sobre libros. Un día me llamo porque se había quedado sin canal, y me ofreció en su oficina de la calle Uriarte, conducir La Pregunta Animal.
Quería entrar al Grupo Clarin con ese programa y después hacer otros. Pensamos nuevamente invitados, escenografía, cortinas, secciones. Lo presentamos, se aprobó pero de un día para el otro desapareció sin avisar!
Telefe apareció y le ofreció Morfi. Y consiguió otro éxito. Ahí nos alejamos, por voluntad y error de ambos, y ya no volvimos a hablar. Nos seguíamos en silencio. Nos mandábamos mensajes por terceros. Al año comenzó LAM, para competir con Morfi, y fue Gerardo quien más FE le tuvo. “Nos van a romper el orto, les va a ir genial, el programa es una bomba” le decía a gente en común, sabiendo que me llegaría. Un año después, nos saludamos fríamente en otro Martín Fierro. Dos bóludos.
Nunca mas hablamos. GERARDO #QEPD❤️

post_Description:
O assédio é um tema que sempre desperta interesse e curiosidade de empresas que desejam entender as melhores condutas para sua prevenção.⁣
⁣
Alguns acham que há uma supervalorização de algumas condutas, com vista à obtenção de indenizações, mas o fato é que o assunto deixou de ser uma conversa para a hora do café ou para se discutir em um processo trabalhista.⁣
⁣
Desde o dia 21 de setembro de 2022, está em vigor uma Lei que obriga todas as empresas a promoverem treinamentos de combate ao assédio, bem como implementar canais para o recebimento de denúncias.⁣
⁣
A Lei nº 14.457/2022, que instituiu o Programa Mais Mulheres, trouxe um capítulo dedicado às medidas de prevenção ao assédio sexual e a outras formas de violência no ambiente de trabalho, o que significa que o assédio moral também deve ser prevenido.⁣
⁣

A IQAir divulgou na terça (14) a análise da qualidade média do ar de 131 países e territórios durante 2022 e alertou que apenas seis países – Austrália, Estônia, Finlândia, Granada, Islândia e Nova Zelândia – e sete territórios no Pacífico e no Caribe, incluindo Guam e Porto Rico, se adequaram aos requisitos e diretrizes de qualidade do ar estabelecidos pela a Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS), que exigem um nível médio de poluição do ar de 5 microgramas por metro cúbico ou menos.⁣
⁣
De acordo com o ranking da IQAir, que tem o Brasil na 57ª posição, oito países excederam, em muito, as diretrizes da OMS para má qualidade do ar, com poluição média acima de 50 microgramas por metro cúbico. ⁣

Um levantamento do Google registrou que 64% dos brasileiros não têm “love brands”, aquelas marcas que não deixam de comprar por nada. O principal motivo para as mudanças na hora de escolher as marcas de consumo é o preço, de acordo com 37% das pessoas.

A pesquisa foi encomendada pela big tech à Offerwise e consultou mais de 2 mil pessoas de todas as idades, classes sociais e regiões do país. O estudo procurou entender a relação que os brasileiros têm com marcas de alimentos, bebidas, produtos de higiene e limpeza.

O resultado mostra o retrato de um quadro econômico desgastado, consequência da crise econômica, inflação em alta e de quebras na cadeia de abastecimento. E também de um cenário mais competitivo: novas marcas como as nativas digitais e aquelas fundadas por criadores de conteúdo surgem diariamente e concorrem com as grandes companhias antes estabelecidas.

A diluição da força das grandes marcas é reforçada por um outro dado do próprio Google.93% das pesquisas sobre produtos na ferramenta de buscas atualmente são genéricas, citam apenas as categorias. As marcas são lembradas nos 7% restantes.

Segundo a pesquisa da Offerwise, apenas 19% dos entrevistados indicaram que consomem sempre as mesmas marcas.

Leia a matéria completa em #exame. Link na bio! ⁣
🖋️ Marcos Bonfim⁣

O BTG Pactual (do mesmo grupo de controle da Exame) anunciou nessa semana um movimento estratégico para acelerar a expansão em wealth management. O banco assinou a aquisição integral do FIS Privatbank, de Luxemburgo, uma das principais praças financeiras da Europa, e que possui uma carteira com 500 milhões de euros (R$ 2,8 bilhões, aproximadamente) sob sua administração. O segmento de gestão de fortunas teve um crescimento explosivo dentro da instituição brasileira nos últimos anos.⁣
⁣
A transação é relevante especialmente pelo momento e localização. O valor da compra ficou em 21,3 milhões de euros, ou cerca de R$ 120 milhões, com prêmio sobre os 11 milhões de euros de patrimônio do FIS. O negócio se encaixa como uma luva no atual ambiente de realocação global de recursos. Nos últimos trimestres, Estados Unidos e Europa já foram os mercados de maior expansão para o BTG Pactual em wealth management. O banco brasileiro está presente no Chile, Argentina, Colômbia, Peru, México, Estados Unidos, Portugal e Reino Unido – e aguarda aprovação regulatória para o escritório da Espanha.⁣
⁣

“Alice, como está o clima hoje?” É assim, conversando com assistentes virtuais em meio à lavoura, que o agronegócio tem aderido à tecnologia de ponta para aumentar a produtividade. A “Alexa da cana-de-açúcar” já existe. Alice é o nome da personagem que assume a inteligência artificial por trás do SaaS (software as a service) criado pela empresa ­Solinftec.⁣
⁣
Colheitadeiras, transbordo — caçamba acoplada aos tratores para receber a cana —, painéis de irrigação, entre outras etapas da safra, todos geram e trocam dados em tempo real para aumentar a produtividade do que virará açúcar e etanol. Nos municípios de Igreja Nova e Marituba, em Alagoas, as duas unidades da Usina Caeté possuem 39.000 hectares de área plantada e coberta pela Alice.⁣

post_Description:
Os preços das carnes caíram nas últimas semanas, com variação abaixo da inflação do período, conforme mostrou o Índice Nacional de Preços ao Consumidor Amplo-15 (IPCA-15), prévia da inflação mensal.⁣
⁣
O IPCA-15 geral subiu 0,69% entre meados de fevereiro e meados de março, segundo divulgado nesta sexta-feira, 24, pelo IBGE.⁣
⁣
Já o preço das carnes, individualmente, caiu 0,91% no período.⁣
⁣
As carnes que mais tiveram queda de preço foram a carne de carneiro (-2,66%), o contrafilé (-2,04%) e a picanha (-1,43%).⁣
⁣
O IPCA-15 diz respeito ao período entre a última quinzena do mês anterior e a primeira quinzena do mês atual, e é considerado uma prévia do IPCA final, que abrange o mês completo e é divulgado no mês seguinte.⁣
⁣
Para o IPCA-15 deste mês, os preços foram coletados no período de 11 de fevereiro a 15 de março (e comparados com os preços vigentes de 13 de janeiro a 10 de fevereiro de 2023).⁣
⁣

Este ano, as vagas de emprego serão remotas e os selecionados terão a opção de trabalhar totalmente em home-office ou de forma híbrida no Centro de Engenharia do Google, em Belo Horizonte.

post_Description:
O Índice Nacional de Preços ao Consumidor Amplo-15 (IPCA-15), prévia da inflação mensal, subiu 0,69% em março, segundo divulgado nesta sexta-feira, 24, pelo IBGE.⁣
⁣
◾ O acumulado em 12 meses ficou em 5,36%;⁣
◾ No acumulado do ano, a partir de janeiro, a variação é de 2,01%.⁣
⁣
A variação dos preços em março representa uma desaceleração frente ao mês anterior: no índice de fevereiro, o IPCA-15 havia subido 0,76%.⁣
⁣
O resultado veio em linha com as expectativas do mercado, que esperava variação em torno de 0,67%.⁣
⁣
Dos nove grupos de produtos e serviços pesquisados, oito tiveram alta no mês de março, com exceção de Artigos de Residência (queda de 0,18%). O maior impacto no índice e a maior alta (1,50%) vieram de Transportes, grupo que inclui os combustíveis.⁣
⁣
O IPCA-15 diz respeito ao período entre a última quinzena do mês anterior e a primeira quinzena do mês atual, e é considerado uma prévia do IPCA final, que abrange o mês completo e é divulgado no mês seguinte. Para o IPCA-15 deste mês, os preços foram coletados no período de 11 de fevereiro a 15 de março e comparados com os preços vigentes de 13 de janeiro a 10 de fevereiro de 2023.⁣
⁣
